Gospel star Emmy Kosgei is renowned for songs in her native Kalenjin tongue that have transcended cultural boundaries, making her one of the most sought-after gospel singers in the East African market. Her brother Meshack Kipkoech, however, is the focus of this tale. He struck and killed a man with his car, and he has been ordered by a court to pay the mother Sh945,000 within 10 days. The money will be awarded to Kotete Chebet, the mother of Andrew Cheruiyot, who died in a road accident along Mogotio-Marigat road in Baringo in 2008. Principal magistrate Bernard Mararo ordered this compensation in lieu of a jail term, which the court lifted, but should he fail to pay...